      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` for all entries where the tour starts with `J09A`.\\n\\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"KSA\\\"`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"`\\n\\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with the `EABLG` table using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the resulting table with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data table entries are not empty:\\n   1. Use the customer data entries from the sales customer data table.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the customer data entries from the net customer data table.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached.\\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_68c5f737-3093-4998-81c9-38fb9309208e"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "56081c9c-01a7-4837-adfa-8e4c7ea03f1f",
        "tool_call_id": "call_V3W23MlahI2GKiZ4qloN1IKZ",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` for all entries where the tour starts with `J09A`.\n\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - if a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"KSA\"`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"`\n\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with the `EABLG` table using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the resulting table with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data table entries are not empty:\n   1. Use the customer data entries from the sales customer data table.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the customer data entries from the net customer data table.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached.\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
